---
// Ecosystem.astro
// Content-addressed artefact ecosystem — registry and contract builder
---

<section class="section reveal" id="ecosystem">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="ecosystem">
      <h2 class="ecosystem__title">Artefact Ecosystem</h2>
      <div class="ecosystem__body">
        <p>
          Every enforcement-relevant artefact — schemas, guardian policies, prompt programs,
          model profiles — is content-addressed (SHA-256 over JCS-canonicalized JSON) and stored
          in a versioned registry. The relay admits only artefacts whose digests it can verify.
          Unknown artefacts are rejected at startup — fail-closed by default.
        </p>
        <p>
          Contracts compose from registry artefacts. The <code>av-contract build</code> CLI
          resolves artefacts by digest, alias, or channel reference, validates SAFE/RICH
          compatibility between schemas and policies, and computes the contract hash. What was
          once a hardcoded template is now an open-ended assembly process.
        </p>
        <p>
          Operators curate registries. Agents compose contracts. Relays admit only what they
          have verified.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .ecosystem {
    max-width: var(--content-max);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .ecosystem__title {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .ecosystem__body p {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    color: var(--color-text);
    max-width: none;
  }

  .ecosystem__body p + p {
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
  }
</style>
